auyaca-waterfalls\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Nauyaca Waterfalls<\/a>. However, they are just a short journey from Uvita and can be visited on a day trip while you stay there. Buses leave from Quepos (near <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/costa-rica\/uvita\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Uvita<\/a>) around 4 times a day and take approximately 2 hours, costing around 5 USD. You can take regular public buses to Quesos (from Manuel Antonio), which take about 30 minutes.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/03220922\/Costa-Rica-2-week-itinerary-3-1.jpg\" alt=\"drive car costa rica\"><\/noscript><img width=\"270\" height=\"338\" alt=\"drive car costa rica\" class=\"wp-image-77642 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1536px) 100vw, 1536px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/03220922\/Costa-Rica-2-week-itinerary-3-1.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/03220922\/Costa-Rica-2-week-itinerary-3-1-480x600.jpg 480w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/03220922\/Costa-Rica-2-week-itinerary-3-1-648x810.jpg 648w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/03220922\/Costa-Rica-2-week-itinerary-3-1-270x338.jpg 270w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/03220922\/Costa-Rica-2-week-itinerary-3-1-24x30.jpg 24w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/03220922\/Costa-Rica-2-week-itinerary-3-1-130x163.jpg 130w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/03220922\/Costa-Rica-2-week-itinerary-3-1-144x180.jpg 144w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/03220922\/Costa-Rica-2-week-itinerary-3-1-614x768.jpg 614w, https:\/\/stati